dismissalText.commentary: Nishan Madushka run out (Hasan Mahmud/†Litton Das) 57 (105b 6x4 0x6 127m) SR: 54.28

dismissalComment.html: Mix-up and do they have the break through here? Yes they do! Sri Lanka have shot themselves in the foot! This was easily cut into the covers, and they ease a single. Madushka thinks there's a second here and turns back, but there's some yes, no, yes. Madushka is sent back when he's already halfway down the pitch. Not even a dive saves him as the throw is brilliant, right over the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Dimuth Karunaratne b Hasan Mahmud 86 (129b 8x4 1x6 228m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Mahmud breaks through! Gentle length delivery, angling across the batter outside off. Karunaratne looks at the width and throws his hands at it. Does not commit to the stroke as well as he would have wanted, though, and because he is playing away from his body, he ends up dragging it back onto his stumps. First wicket in Test cricket for Mahmud, and this is just what Bangladesh would have wanted before the tea interval!

dismissalText.long: c KNM Fernando b PHKD Mendis
dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c KNM Fernando b PHKD Mendis 36 (53b 3x4 0x6 106m) SR: 67.92

dismissalComment.html: sharp catch at gully. Kamindu gets the breakthrough! That's his first Test wicket and Kamindu is ecstatic. What a series he's had. It's the turn he generates that surprised Shakib. This was a flattish delivery that pitched outside off and was turning away. Shakib tried to open the face and carve it through point, but it's turned more than he expected and it comes off a thick outside edge and flies very quickly to Madushka who does well to cling on near his shoulder. Shakib is livid at himself.
